author: TNN

The initiative focuses on raising awareness, providing access via RBI's UDGAM portal, and ensuring officials actively help claimants reclaim their forgotten money.

author: DURGESH NANDAN JHA AND AMARJEET SINGH
description: Eleven children died in MP's Chhindwara from renal failure after consuming cough syrup. A lab report confirmed Coldrif syrup contained 48.6% diethylene glycol, a poisonous industrial chemical. This prompted MP to ban the medicine and other products from its manufacturer, Sresan Pharmaceuticals, while multi-state checks on drug units are now underway.

author: TNN

author: SRISHTI LAKHOTIA
description: Bengal houses the highest number of foreign prisoners in India, with 2,508 inmates, primarily Bangladeshis detained for illegal entry. These foreigners constitute 9% of the state's total prison population, contributing to severe overcrowding at 120% occupancy. Low deportation rates and a large shared border exacerbate the issue, with many being undertrials.

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: Alcohol has long been a part of social and cultural life, but the question of how much is truly safe remains complex. Science shows that alcohol has a biphasic effect — small amounts may offer some cardiovascular benefits, while higher intakes, even occasional, can harm the heart, liver, brain, and overall health. Individual factors like genetics, sex, and metabolism influence how the body processes alcohol, making “safe” levels vary from person to person.
title: What is the permissible amount of alcohol that can be consumed without harm

This followed days of violence and unrest in the region. The deal includes compensation for victims and significant developmental measures. Key provisions cover education, health, and electricity improvements. Administrative reforms and infrastructure projects are also part of the agreement.
title: '38-point charter': Pak govt reaches agreement with protestors on 25 points

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Meta is aggressively pushing employees to adopt AI tools, deploying tracking dashboards and a gamified system to monitor usage. This aligns with similar mandates from Google and Microsoft, making AI proficiency a critical workplace expectation. Some Meta departments, like Reality Labs, face ambitious adoption targets, influencing performance. This industry-wide shift underscores that embracing AI is crucial for career progression and company competitiveness in Silicon Valley's rapidly evolving tech landscape.
title: Meta’s AI ultimatum: Company sends Google, Microsoft-like warning; be more AI-savvy…

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Chief Justice of India B R Gavai affirmed in Mauritius that India's legal system operates under the rule of law, not "bulldozer justice," citing his verdict against executive overreach. He underscored the Supreme Court's role in upholding this principle through landmark judgments, ensuring equality and human dignity. Gavai emphasized the rule of law as an evolving ethical framework guiding governance.
title: 'Not bulldozer justice': CJI Gavai says legal system governed by rule of law

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi unveiled youth-centric initiatives exceeding Rs 62,000 crore, significantly impacting poll-bound Bihar. Key launches include the Rs 60,000 crore PM-SETU scheme to modernize ITIs, new vocational labs, and enhanced financial aid for students. Modi also inaugurated a skill university and dedicated NIT Patna's Bihta campus, underscoring a commitment to youth empowerment and skill development.
title: Poll-bound Bihar in focus: PM unveils Rs 62,000cr youth-focused initiatives

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: US trade representative Jamieson Greer claimed India is diversifying from Russian oil, despite a 50% tariff imposed, half of which targets India's recent surge in Russian oil purchases. Conversely, Russian President Vladimir Putin asserted India will continue energy imports from Russia, suggesting increased Russian imports of Indian goods to balance trade.
title: ‘Starting to diversify’: Is India cutting back on Russian oil? What Trump aide said

author: TOI Education
description: A circulating affidavit claims UPSC will release provisional answer keys for the Civil Services Prelims immediately after the exam, inviting candidate objections before finalisation. However, UPSC Chairman Dr Ajay Kumar clarified no such change is official yet. The matter is sub-judice before the Supreme Court, and candidates are advised to rely only on UPSC’s official notifications.
title: UPSC answer key: Will it be published before prelims results? What we know so fa

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: The US government shutdown continues for a third day. Military families face financial anxiety and seek food assistance. White House Press Secretary Karoline Leavitt highlights impacts on 1.3 million service members unpaid. WIC programs and air traffic controllers also face jeopardy. The shutdown could cost the US economy billions weekly. Lawmakers have not reached a resolution.
title: US shutdown: Military families seek food aid as WH warns of wider impact

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Bollywood stars Vijay Deverakonda and Rashmika Mandanna have officially confirmed their engagement, sending fans into a frenzy. Vijay's team verified the news on Saturday, leading to widespread celebration online. The couple, who reportedly began dating in 2018 after 'Geetha Govindam', had previously kept their relationship private. Fans are now showering the beloved pair with congratulations.
title: Vijay Deverakonda & Rashmika Mandanna engaged; fans react

author: TOI Education
description: A coalition of unions, educators, and advocacy groups has filed the first major lawsuit against President Trump’s $100,000 H-1B visa fee, calling it unlawful and harmful to US industries. Filed in California federal court, the case challenges presidential authority, citing risks to innovation, healthcare, and education. The outcome could reshape immigration policy and global talent flow.
title: First major legal challenge hits Trump’s $100K H-1B visa overhaul - Here’s what to know

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Two Indian men, Arokkiyasami Daison and Rajendran Mayilarasan, were sentenced to five years and one month in prison with 12 strokes of the cane in Singapore. They pleaded guilty to assaulting and robbing two women in hotel rooms after being approached by a man offering sex workers. The men cited financial hardship as their motive for the crimes.
title: Cash & jewellery looted: 2 Indians arrested for robbing sex workers in Singapore hotel

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Hamas partially accepted Donald Trump's Gaza peace plan, agreeing to release all Israeli hostages if conditions are met. However, the group seeks further negotiations on crucial clauses concerning Gaza's future governance, Israeli withdrawal, and its own role. Trump urged Israel to halt bombing for hostage release, while warning of severe consequences if the deal ultimately fails.
title: Hostage release but ... : Hamas agrees to Trump’s Gaza peace plan with conditions - What are they?

author: TNN
description: Singer Zubeen Garg died under mysterious circumstances. His manager Siddharth Sharma faces arrest. Witnesses allege poisoning and criminal conspiracy. Sharma reportedly dismissed symptoms during Garg's final moments. He allegedly controlled the yacht and supplied liquor. Other statements corroborate Sharma's actions. Financial records and witness accounts establish culpability. Police now treat this as a premeditated murder.
title: ‘Jabo de’: Bandmate recalls Zubeen Garg’s final moments; alleges he was frothing at mouth

author: TOI SCIENCE DESK
description: NASA scales back most operations due to a US government funding deadlock. This action impacts many ongoing projects. Essential tasks like monitoring astronauts on the ISS continue. However, research and mission planning face delays. Programmes like Artemis could see postponed timelines. Past shutdowns show similar disruptions. This situation affects global scientific collaboration.
title: Nasa shuts down: Why the oldest space agency has stopped functioning

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Priyanka Gandhi Vadra criticized the Centre for approving only ₹260 crore for Wayanad landslide relief, a fraction of Kerala's ₹2,221 crore request. She stressed that human suffering should not be politicized. Meanwhile, CM Pinarayi Vijayan stated the sanctioned funds haven't arrived, and Kerala's demands for national disaster status and loan waivers remain unaddressed.
title: 'Relief must rise above politics': Priyanka hits out at Centre after Wayanad floods

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Chicago Alderperson Jessie Fuentes was shoved and handcuffed by federal immigration agents at a medical center while questioning their warrant. Mayor Brandon Johnson condemned ICE's "abusive tactics," asserting officials' right to document actions. This incident highlights increased, militarized immigration enforcement in Humboldt Park, drawing widespread condemnation from local leaders and organizations.
title: Watch: Chicago official shoved and handcuffed by ICE at hospital

author: PRABIN KALITA
description: The investigation into singer Zubeen Garg's death intensified as bandmate Shekhar Jyoti Goswami alleged manager Siddharth Sharma and organiser Shyamkanu Mahanta poisoned him. Sharma, Mahanta, Goswami, and co-singer Amritprabha Mahanta were arrested, with murder charges now added. Zubeen's wife also questioned the circumstances surrounding his death in Singapore, as the SIT continues its sensitive probe.
title: Accident or murder? Zubeen Garg’s bandmate levels big allegations; claims manager ‘poisoned’ singer

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: An ECI delegation, led by CEC Gyanesh Kumar, arrived in Patna to review preparations for the upcoming Bihar Assembly elections, holding an all-party meeting. This follows a briefing for Central Observers, whom Kumar called "beacons of democracy" for ensuring free and fair polls. Bihar's election dates are expected to be announced on October 6 or 7.
title: Bihar elections: CEC-led EC delegation arrives in Patna; reviews poll preparations

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: India controlled the opening Test against West Indies on Day 3. Nitish Reddy made a catch at square leg. This removed Tagenarine Chanderpaul. India declared their innings at 448 for 5. KL Rahul, Dhruv Jurel, and Ravindra Jadeja reached 100 runs. West Indies faced a large run difference. India looked set for a quick win.
title: Full-stretch magic! Nitish Reddy blinder steals the show – Watch

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: Uttar Pradesh opposition leader Mata Prasad Pandey was barred from visiting Bareilly by police, who cited potential disruption following recent "I Love Mohammad" protests. The administration had suspended internet services and arrested 81 individuals, including IMC leaders, after violent demonstrations. Pandey criticized the move, claiming authorities were hiding their shortcomings.
title: 'I love Mohammad' row: SP delegation stopped from Bareily visit

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: Assam's ambitious ₹6,000 crore underwater tunnel project, India's first under a major river, cnnecting Numaligarh and Gohpur, awaits Union cabinet approval. Expected to take five years, it will facilitate both road and rail traffic, significantly boosting regional connectivity and defence capabilities.
title: India's first underwater Brahmaputra tunnel likely to get Cabinet nod- top facts

author: GLOBAL SPORTS DESK
description: Homeland Security Secretary Kristi Noem pledges a strong law enforcement presence at Super Bowl LX. This includes immigration authorities at Levi's Stadium. Her remarks follow Bad Bunny's U.S. tour boycott due to ICE concerns. Noem also criticized the NFL for featuring the reggaeton star. This situation shows the intersection of law enforcement, entertainment, and politics.
title: Kristi Noem pledges heavy ICE deployment at Super Bowl LX amid halftime controversy

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: A viral clip showing cricketer Shoaib Malik and actress Sana Javed sitting silently at an event has fueled speculation about their relationship. This comes after Malik's recent divorce from Sania Mirza and his subsequent marriage to Javed in January 2024. Social media is buzzing with questions, though the couple remains silent amidst varied public reactions.
title: Sania Mirza’s ex Shoaib Malik to divorce third wife? Video sparks breakup rumours

author: SEHJAL GUPTA
description: Emma Raducanu publicly supported Taylor Swift's new album, "The Life of a Showgirl," on Instagram on October 3, 2025, amidst its mixed reception. This gesture followed Raducanu's mixed 2025 tennis season, which included recent losses but also a strong semifinal performance. Her musical interests connect her with fans beyond the court.
title: Emma Raducanu’s IG nod to Taylor Swift’s ‘The Life of a Showgirl’

author: KAUTILYA SINGH
description: A 22-year-old senior deck cadet, Karandeep Singh Rana, went missing from a merchant navy vessel. The ship was traveling from Iraq to China via Sri Lanka and Singapore. His family last contacted him on September 20. The shipping company confirmed his disappearance overboard. A 96-hour search operation was conducted. The vessel is now heading to China for a full investigation.
title: U'khand: 22-yr-old merchant navy’s senior deck cadet goes missing at sea; search ops on

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: The Trump administration offers $2,500 to unaccompanied migrant children aged 14 and above. This stipend encourages their voluntary return to home countries. The Department of Homeland Security issued this offer. Critics label the move as cruel and coercive. However, officials state it provides children with a choice. Payments occur after judicial approval and safe return.
title: $2,500 for 'self-deportation': Trump's offer for unaccompanied migrant kids

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Mohsin Naqvi, Pakistan's Interior Minister and cricket chief, is set to receive the Shaheed Zulfiqar Ali Bhutto Excellence Gold Medal. The award recognizes his principled stance during the Asia Cup final trophy handover, where he retained the trophy after Indian players refused to accept it.
title: Asia Cup: Mohsin Naqvi to receive top national honour for snubbing India trophy

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Munich Airport halted operations twice in 24 hours due to unconfirmed drone sightings, disrupting travel for thousands of passengers with suspensions, diversions, and cancellations. This incident follows similar disruptions across Europe, occurring amidst heightened alerts over alleged Russian drone activity and incursions into NATO airspace. EU leaders are now strengthening defenses against such threats.
title: Drone scare: Munich airport operations suspended for second day; flights disrupted

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: ​After nearly two years of relentless war, the people of Gaza, who have endured daily airstrikes, displacement, and the constant shadow of violence, may be seeing a fragile moment of relief. US President Donald Trump, with his characteristic bluntness, has ordered Israel to stop bombing; Hamas, in a rare gesture, has signaled partial acceptance of a plan.
title: Hamas agrees to free Israeli hostages; Trump asks Israel to stop bombing Gaza — Key things to know

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: The FDA has approved Inluriyo, a first-in-class oral therapy for ESR1-mutated advanced breast cancer, marking a significant breakthrough. This new drug targets hormone-resistant tumors by blocking estrogen receptors, reducing the risk of disease progression or death by 33-38%. Inluriyo offers a convenient pill alternative, bringing new hope to patients.
title: Ray of hope for advanced breast cancer patients: US approves new oral drug Inluriyo

author: TNN
description: Rajasthan ATS apprehended former NSG commando Bajrang Singh, wanted in a 200kg ganja smuggling case. Singh, who served in the 26/11 Mumbai operation and retired in 2021, became a narcotics kingpin, leveraging local connections after failed political ambitions. He was tracked for two months using technical intelligence and informers, culminating in his arrest under 'Operation Gaanjaney'.
title: ‘Op Gaanjaney’: How ATS tracked ex-NSG commando in 200kg drug bust; kingpin had political ambitions

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: US President Donald Trump's new $100,000 fee for H-1B visas faces a federal lawsuit filed by unions, employers, and religious groups. Plaintiffs argue Trump lacks authority to unilaterally impose such a fee, which they claim could foster corruption and stifle innovation.
title: 'Arbitrary, capricious': Lawsuit filed against Trump’s H-1B visa fee hike

author: BARSHA DUTTA
description: Former LSU player Kyren Lacy's suicide, ahead of negligent homicide charges, sparks controversy. His attorney, Matt Ory, challenges the Louisiana State Police investigation into a fatal accident. New surveillance footage reportedly shows Lacy was back in his lane before impact, contradicting official accounts. Ory cites inconsistencies and missing witness testimony, suggesting evidence doesn't support Lacy's culpability, deepening the tragedy.
title: Ex-LSU receiver Kyren Lacy’s lawyer says he is wrongly blamed in fatal crash

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Prime Minister Modi welcomed Donald Trump's Gaza peace plan, calling it a significant step towards ending the conflict. Trump issued an ultimatum to Hamas to accept the 20-point deal by Sunday evening, warning of severe repercussions if they refuse. He claimed the plan, which includes sparing Hamas fighters, has global backing for lasting Middle East peace.
title: 'Significant step forward': PM Modi hails Trump's Gaza peace plan; affirms India's support

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: During their training session at R Premadasa Stadium on Friday, the Indian women's cricket team encountered a non-venomous common rat snake. This familiar reptile, often seen at the venue, moved along drains, creating a light-hearted moment for players and staff. India is preparing for their World Cup match against Pakistan.
title: Ahead of Pak game, snake scare headlines India training session

author: BARSHA DUTTA
description: Arthur Jones, the Super Bowl champion and brother to Jon and Chandler Jones, passed away at 39 on October 3, 2025. Despite gross NFL earnings exceeding $20 million, his estimated net worth in 2025 is $4-8 million after deductions and career setbacks. He is remembered for his positive impact beyond finances.
title: Arthur Jones’ 2025 net worth: Contracts, career earnings & financial legacy

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Los Angeles City Hall was evacuated Friday afternoon after a car crashed into its steps. Police are attempting to contact the driver, who displayed a sign reading "I need ur help" and referencing Donald Trump. The mayor's office confirmed the evacuation out of caution, with no immediate injuries reported.
title: Car rams steps of Los Angeles City Hall; cardboard sign has message for Trump

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: Scientists converted a type A kidney into a type O universal donor kidney. Enzymes removed specific antigens from the organ. The converted kidney worked normally for two days in a brain-dead patient. Antigens then reappeared. This research shows a path to reduce kidney transplant waiting times. It could benefit many type O patients.
title: Kidney transplant breakthrough: Scientists create universal donor to fight shortage

author: NEHA MADAAN
description: The season's first Arabian Sea cyclonic storm, 'Shakhti', intensified on Friday, currently positioned west-southwest of Dwarka. Expected to become a severe cyclonic storm, it is unlikely to significantly impact Indian landmass, though remnants may bring rain to Gujarat. Sea conditions will be very rough, prompting warnings for fishermen. Meanwhile, Maharashtra anticipates light to moderate rain due to another system.
title: Season’s first cyclone, ‘Shakhti’, forms over Arabian Sea; IMD warns of high sea activity

author: SEHJAL GUPTA
description: Former NFL star and Super Bowl champion Arthur Jones died suddenly at 39, with his cause of death unconfirmed. A key defensive player in the Baltimore Ravens' Super Bowl XLVII victory, his passing deeply saddened the sports world. Jones, from a renowned athletic family, is remembered for his positive spirit and legacy.
title: Arthur Jones cause of death: How did the Ravens’ Super Bowl champion die at 39

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Former Pakistan cricketer Mohammad Yousuf has publicly supported ACC chief Mohsin Naqvi amidst the Asia Cup trophy controversy. India, after winning the 2025 final, declined to receive the trophy from Naqvi, prompting BCCI to demand his removal. Yousuf criticized India's refusal as 'filmy,' asserting they should have accepted it as per rules, underscoring escalating tensions between the cricket boards.
title: Asia Cup drama: 'What Naqvi is doing is absolutely right' - PCB chief gets backing

author: RAJ SHEKHAR JHA
description: Pro-Khalistan elements twice attacked an Ontario cinema, attempting arson and firing gunshots, leading the theatre to halt Hindi movie screenings. Designated terror group SFJ subsequently demanded Canada ban all "Made In India" films, alleging they are political weapons for Modi's regime. The theatre CEO confirmed halting Indian films due to safety concerns following these targeted incidents.
title: Canada: Khalistan radicals try to set fire to Ontario cinema; twice in a week

author: SABI HUSSAIN
description: Stray dog attacks at the World Para Athletics Championships in New Delhi raised serious safety concerns after two foreign coaches and a security guard were bitten on Friday. These incidents, following previous unreported attacks, disrupted the event. Despite efforts to clear the stadium, individuals feeding dogs led to their re-entry, prompting strengthened preventive measures.
title: Horrific! Stray dogs attack foreign coaches; fifth incident at JLN stadium

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: A suspected terror attack outside a Manchester synagogue on Yom Kippur left two Jewish men dead and three injured. Police fatally shot assailant Jihad Al-Shamie, 35, a British national of Syrian descent, who was on bail for rape and possibly influenced by extreme Islamist ideology. Six others were arrested on terror charges.
title: Manchester synagogue attack: Police say suspect on bail in rape case- Key points

author: REMA NAGARAJAN
description: The National Medical Commission (NMC) has yet to act against 30 doctors found guilty of accepting a foreign trip funded by pharma company AbbVie. This delay stems from four out of five vacant posts in its Ethics and Medical Registration Board, hindering action. NMC's new chairperson confirmed the issue, stating a temporary board is being considered to address pending matters.
title: National Medical Commission still to act on junketeering doctors

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: The US government shutdown entered its third day with no resolution as Republican and Democratic leaders remain deadlocked. Republicans insist on their short-term funding bill, while Democrats refuse without their input, citing public opinion blaming the GOP. Both parties' bills have failed, and the GOP needs five more Democratic votes to advance their proposal.
title: US government shutdown extended after Senate votes fail again

author: TNN
description: GST reduction on 375 items boosted consumer spending. Navratri sales reached a decade high. Government officials cited industry data. Families upgraded vehicles and bought white goods. This turned festive cheer into record consumption. Brands and retailers reported sales growth. This provided a boost for India's consumption-driven economy. Car bookings also saw an increase.
title: GST cuts: Navratri sales hit 10-year high; retailers report 25-100% sales growth
